.TH "drm_atomic_helper_crtc_reset" 9 "drm_atomic_helper_crtc_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_atomic_helper_crtc_reset \- default &drm_crtc_funcs.reset hook for CRTCs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_atomic_helper_crtc_reset
.BI "(struct drm_crtc *crtc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "crtc" 12
drm CRTC
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Resets the atomic state for \fIcrtc\fP by freeing the state pointer (which might
be NULL, e.g. at driver load time) and allocating a new empty state object.
